  "instructions": [
    "Combine tinned tomatoes, namul-blanch season, rice vinegar, sugar, and water in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a saucepan and bring to a simmer over medium heat.",
    "Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Strain the mixture through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, pressing on the solids to extract as much liquid as possible.",
    "Stir in chopped cilantro, salt, and black pepper.",
    "To assemble the bowls, place a scoop of brown rice on the bottom, followed by a spoonful of the fermented tomatoes, chopped avocado, pickled mustard seeds, and chopped scallions.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
